{"word":"G5429 - φρόνιμος - phrónimos - fron'-ee-mos - Wise","slug":"G5429","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">φρόνιμος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>phrónimos"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>fron'-ee-mos"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Wise"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C6;&#x03C1;&#x03BF;&#x0301;&#x03BD;&#x03B9;&#x03BC;&#x03BF;&#x03C2; - phronimos</b> - <i>fron'-ee-mos</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G5424\">G5424</a>; <i>thoughtful</i>, that is, <i>sagacious</i> or <i>discreet</i> (implying a <i>cautious</i> character; while <a href=\"#/G4680\">G4680</a> denotes <i>practical</i> skill or acumen; and <a href=\"#/G4908\">G4908</a> indicates rather <i>intelligence</i> or mental acquirement); in a bad sense <i>conceited</i> (also in the comparative): - wise (-r)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G5424\">G5424</a>, <a href=\"#/G5426\">G5426</a>, <a href=\"#/G5427\">G5427</a>, <a href=\"#/G5428\">G5428</a>, <a href=\"#/G5430\">G5430</a>, <a href=\"#/G877\">G877</a>, <a href=\"#/G878\">G878</a>"}]}